features: 【Premium PET Sleeved PSU Cables】Woven with nylon material, more heat-resistant than cotton mesh, will not cause heat shrinkage, PET fiber is also more robust, maintaining better durability while the color is more vibrant,match well with other colors of the case, when paired with a white case, revealing a sense of elegance and neatness, more beautiful.

【Excellent Stability】High specification 16 AWG cable core,adopt thicker tinned copper,can keep the voltage stable,and will not heat up even through high current,easily handle your ultra high power computer power supply(800W-1600W).

【Coloured Transparent Connectors】The adapter of the sleeved cable extension kit is made of ABS transparent material,which has the advantages of anti-aging,compression,deformation,high temperature resistance,flame retardant,and clearly see the construction of the terminals;at the same time,this material is smoother and more finely shaped than the general connectors.

【EASY CABLE MANAGEMENT】Design for one way curve,longer length on top and the shorter on the bottom,easy to organize your cables.Note：the（6+2Pin）graphics card cable snaps inner the arc,It is recommended to route the wiring to the top of the graphics card.
【Cable Extension PC Includes】1×24-pin ATX, 2×4+4pin EPS, 3X6+2Pin PCI-E, suitable for high power GPU and graphics card power supplies.
body.description: SIRLYR PSU Cables Sleeved Cable Extension Kit Premium Power PSU individually braided cable extensions with sleeving, fully shielded and multi-layered 16AWG high quality copper wire. PC cable combs ensure cable separation and increased airflow while maintaining an organized look inside your PC and keeping your cables neatly aligned.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They're pretty good.
reviews.reviewText: I had bought cable extensions at a similar price point ~$25 previously and these do feel a step above those in terms of connector and cable wrap quality. The wires are pretty flexible which was an issue with the other set I had. That set was too stiff with lower quality connections and would eventually shake themselves loose from the PSU cables and result in GPU crashes under load due to imperfect power delivery.Not an issue for me, but the lengths of the 2+6 PCIE wires do appear to be slightly different for the top/bottom 4, which allows for even bends but if you're hoping to have the cable completely straight for some reason, that might be an issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great looking extension, but curve only one way.
reviews.reviewText: Really up the aesthetic and organization of the build. Everything power up fine, but we will have to see how it hold up in the long term.Many review pointed out that cable are uneven, but they are design that way for one way bend/curve. As you bend the longer length suppose to be on top and the shorter on the bottom. This will limit the way you organize your cables and how the build will look. For example, originally I wanted to have the gpu cable extension to come from bottom cut out of the case but I couldn't as the cable only bend one way and the power pins only clip in one way. Therefore, I had to lay them on top the gpu. I could have force the bend and make it work like how I originally wanted but the opposite end cable would be an uneven mess which would ruin the aesthetic and defeat the purpose of this cable. But my build still turn out great, soooo 4 out of 5.
